WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.780 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.780 --> 00:00:07.670 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY DYER: Is there a
hidden, more esoteric,

00:00:07.670 --> 00:00:09.500 align:middle line:84%
deeper meaning to
the Hollywood films

00:00:09.500 --> 00:00:11.330 align:middle line:90%
that we all love to watch?

00:00:11.330 --> 00:00:12.350 align:middle line:90%
I'm Jay Dyer.

00:00:12.350 --> 00:00:13.808 align:middle line:84%
>>JAY WEIDNER: And
I'm Jay Weidner,

00:00:13.808 --> 00:00:15.849 align:middle line:90%
and this is "Hollywood Decoded."

00:00:15.849 --> 00:00:19.202 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:19.202 --> 00:00:25.775 align:middle line:90%


00:00:25.775 --> 00:00:27.150 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: Today
we're going to look

00:00:27.150 --> 00:00:29.220 align:middle line:90%
at "Artificial Intelligence."

00:00:29.220 --> 00:00:32.009 align:middle line:84%
This is the retelling
of the Pinocchio story

00:00:32.009 --> 00:00:35.357 align:middle line:84%
by Spielberg adapted from
the Stanley Kubrick script.

00:00:35.357 --> 00:00:37.440 align:middle line:84%
And then we're going to
look at "Minority Report."

00:00:37.440 --> 00:00:39.420 align:middle line:84%
This is another
Spielberg film, this time

00:00:39.420 --> 00:00:43.350 align:middle line:84%
adapted from dystopian gnostic
writer, Philip K Dick, that

00:00:43.350 --> 00:00:45.600 align:middle line:84%
pictures a future
when everything

00:00:45.600 --> 00:00:47.100 align:middle line:90%
is tracked and traced.

00:00:47.100 --> 00:00:49.320 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Well, we know
that this was originally

00:00:49.320 --> 00:00:53.490 align:middle line:84%
going to be a one-two punch
ending of Stanley Kubrick's

00:00:53.490 --> 00:00:54.550 align:middle line:90%
career.

00:00:54.550 --> 00:00:57.480 align:middle line:10%
He was going to put out
"Eyes Wide Shut" in 1999,

00:00:57.480 --> 00:00:59.730 align:middle line:10%
and then finish up on
the year of his most

00:00:59.730 --> 00:01:03.610 align:middle line:10%
famous film, "2001," and he
was going to release "AI."

00:01:03.610 --> 00:01:06.810 align:middle line:84%
And he'd been working
on it for years

00:01:06.810 --> 00:01:10.590 align:middle line:84%
with Ian Watson and various
other science fiction writers.

00:01:10.590 --> 00:01:15.210 align:middle line:84%
And the story is that Spielberg,
who was friends with Stanley,

00:01:15.210 --> 00:01:18.450 align:middle line:84%
was given the script
by Stanley to do,

00:01:18.450 --> 00:01:22.920 align:middle line:84%
because Kubrick was very private
about everything that he did.

00:01:22.920 --> 00:01:25.890 align:middle line:84%
And I mean, I do believe he did
give the script to Spielberg,

00:01:25.890 --> 00:01:27.550 align:middle line:90%
but just to get an opinion.

00:01:27.550 --> 00:01:30.660 align:middle line:84%
And so I actually
have an insider,

00:01:30.660 --> 00:01:33.000 align:middle line:84%
who has told me what
Kubrick's script was going

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:38.070 align:middle line:84%
to be about on "AI," and we
got the results of Spielberg's

00:01:38.070 --> 00:01:40.020 align:middle line:84%
"AI," which we're
going to discuss.

00:01:40.020 --> 00:01:42.240 align:middle line:84%
And they're completely
different films,

00:01:42.240 --> 00:01:48.690 align:middle line:84%
and I find it curious,
because as my insider told

00:01:48.690 --> 00:01:52.530 align:middle line:84%
me, when I was talking to him
in 2001, right after this film

00:01:52.530 --> 00:01:56.500 align:middle line:84%
came out, he told me,
what kind of person

00:01:56.500 --> 00:01:59.880 align:middle line:84%
would really want to own a
perpetual 12-year-old boy

00:01:59.880 --> 00:02:00.960 align:middle line:90%
or girl?

00:02:00.960 --> 00:02:03.420 align:middle line:84%
And would a mother
really want to have

00:02:03.420 --> 00:02:06.660 align:middle line:84%
a boy that never grows older,
never matures, never goes

00:02:06.660 --> 00:02:09.030 align:middle line:90%
to college or gets married?

00:02:09.030 --> 00:02:11.320 align:middle line:90%
And I thought, no.

00:02:11.320 --> 00:02:15.420 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, well, that kind
of fits in a bookend way what

00:02:15.420 --> 00:02:16.860 align:middle line:90%
"Eyes Wide Shut" is implying.

00:02:16.860 --> 00:02:17.250 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Right.

00:02:17.250 --> 00:02:18.050 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Right?

00:02:18.050 --> 00:02:20.280 align:middle line:84%
So I thought, wow, we
really missed a big one here

00:02:20.280 --> 00:02:26.100 align:middle line:84%
when Kubrick died in 1999
and did not get to make "AI."

00:02:26.100 --> 00:02:30.780 align:middle line:84%
Spielberg's "AI" is a
very different film,

00:02:30.780 --> 00:02:34.440 align:middle line:84%
and I'm glad that he made it,
because it gave me insights

00:02:34.440 --> 00:02:37.510 align:middle line:84%
into him, more
than anything else.

00:02:37.510 --> 00:02:39.180 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: So "Artificial
Intelligence"

00:02:39.180 --> 00:02:42.240 align:middle line:84%
is operating just like "Blade
Runner" on many levels.

00:02:42.240 --> 00:02:45.660 align:middle line:84%
We have this fairy tale, and
fairy tales come up many times

00:02:45.660 --> 00:02:46.530 align:middle line:90%
in the film.

00:02:46.530 --> 00:02:47.910 align:middle line:84%
But it's not your
typical fairy tale.

00:02:47.910 --> 00:02:48.960 align:middle line:90%
It's not just Pinocchio.

00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:52.710 align:middle line:84%
It's a specific
reorganization and retelling

00:02:52.710 --> 00:02:54.180 align:middle line:90%
of the gnostic mythology.

00:02:54.180 --> 00:02:56.100 align:middle line:84%
And we know from
Spielberg's penchant

00:02:56.100 --> 00:02:58.220 align:middle line:84%
with using Philip
K Dick, as we're

00:02:58.220 --> 00:02:59.970 align:middle line:84%
going to see in "Minority
Report," that he

00:02:59.970 --> 00:03:03.000 align:middle line:84%
has no problem with a
gnostic retelling of stories.

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:07.890 align:middle line:84%
So what I see this as is,
basically, a combination,

00:03:07.890 --> 00:03:10.530 align:middle line:84%
a coalescence of a whole
bunch of fairy tales

00:03:10.530 --> 00:03:12.870 align:middle line:84%
that tell the story
of transhumanism

00:03:12.870 --> 00:03:16.350 align:middle line:84%
repackaged, as we said,
from Pinocchio, and then

00:03:16.350 --> 00:03:18.750 align:middle line:84%
in a weird way,
kind of dehumanizing

00:03:18.750 --> 00:03:20.674 align:middle line:90%
humans and humanizing the bots.

00:03:20.674 --> 00:03:22.590 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we're
going to see, especially

00:03:22.590 --> 00:03:25.980 align:middle line:84%
when David is shown in his
Edenic state with his mom.

00:03:25.980 --> 00:03:28.620 align:middle line:84%
He has this very perfect,
as we said, golden era,

00:03:28.620 --> 00:03:32.630 align:middle line:84%
golden age fairy
tale primeval state,

00:03:32.630 --> 00:03:34.770 align:middle line:84%
and then he falls
into understanding

00:03:34.770 --> 00:03:36.790 align:middle line:90%
that the world is a mess.

00:03:36.790 --> 00:03:38.770 align:middle line:90%
The world is the flesh fair.

00:03:38.770 --> 00:03:40.730 align:middle line:90%


00:03:40.730 --> 00:03:43.020 align:middle line:84%
This is a very
Dante-esque inferno scene,

00:03:43.020 --> 00:03:45.930 align:middle line:84%
where everybody's
torturing the bots,

00:03:45.930 --> 00:03:48.960 align:middle line:84%
and Spielberg tries to
evoke that Holocaust imagery

00:03:48.960 --> 00:03:51.000 align:middle line:84%
with references to
the Holocaust by some

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:52.860 align:middle line:90%
of the bots in that scene.

00:03:52.860 --> 00:03:56.500 align:middle line:10%
And so then it takes us on this
long journey to Rouge City,

00:03:56.500 --> 00:03:59.490 align:middle line:10%
and then we experience the
baser desires of humanity

00:03:59.490 --> 00:04:02.490 align:middle line:10%
with these entire
cities and buildings

00:04:02.490 --> 00:04:04.504 align:middle line:10%
that are giant horrors
and strumpets bent over.

00:04:04.504 --> 00:04:06.420 align:middle line:84%
I mean, we're going to
see all kinds of really

00:04:06.420 --> 00:04:07.980 align:middle line:84%
bizarre crazy things
in this movie,

00:04:07.980 --> 00:04:10.080 align:middle line:90%
and then it goes into aliens.

00:04:10.080 --> 00:04:11.950 align:middle line:90%
So what do you think?

00:04:11.950 --> 00:04:14.316 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Well, I think
it's a number of things,

00:04:14.316 --> 00:04:16.649 align:middle line:84%
and one of the things that
I'm going to keep coming back

00:04:16.649 --> 00:04:20.519 align:middle line:84%
to this theme throughout the
show that we do continuously,

00:04:20.519 --> 00:04:23.880 align:middle line:84%
and that is the process
of individuation.

00:04:23.880 --> 00:04:30.840 align:middle line:84%
And David, again, the robot,
he is asleep in a lot of ways.

00:04:30.840 --> 00:04:32.910 align:middle line:84%
And it isn't until
his mom leaves him,

00:04:32.910 --> 00:04:34.590 align:middle line:84%
or she leaves him
out in the woods,

00:04:34.590 --> 00:04:37.530 align:middle line:84%
and then he begins that
Holocaust and that journey,

00:04:37.530 --> 00:04:40.500 align:middle line:84%
that he begins to realize
that he's an individual.

00:04:40.500 --> 00:04:42.780 align:middle line:84%
And then when he finally
meets the blue fairy,

00:04:42.780 --> 00:04:46.080 align:middle line:84%
because he has a mission,
which none of the other robots

00:04:46.080 --> 00:04:49.650 align:middle line:84%
ever have, he has a mission to
see the blue fairy, which used

00:04:49.650 --> 00:04:52.690 align:middle line:90%
to be a statue in Coney Island.

00:04:52.690 --> 00:04:54.600 align:middle line:90%
But now it's under water.

00:04:54.600 --> 00:04:57.330 align:middle line:84%
And on the way, he
meets Dr. Hobby,

00:04:57.330 --> 00:05:00.210 align:middle line:84%
who is, of course, the
alchemist who made him.

00:05:00.210 --> 00:05:01.920 align:middle line:84%
And we find out
that David is made

00:05:01.920 --> 00:05:05.280 align:middle line:84%
in the image of his lost
son, which, again, is

00:05:05.280 --> 00:05:07.890 align:middle line:90%
a very kind of alchemist thing.

00:05:07.890 --> 00:05:12.570 align:middle line:84%
And David reacts in a way
like, no, I'm not just that.

00:05:12.570 --> 00:05:13.920 align:middle line:90%
I'm more than that.

00:05:13.920 --> 00:05:16.110 align:middle line:84%
And then he takes his
plunge into the water.

00:05:16.110 --> 00:05:19.050 align:middle line:84%
So I think this really is about
the process of individuation,

00:05:19.050 --> 00:05:22.260 align:middle line:84%
which is why we like
these kinds of movies,

00:05:22.260 --> 00:05:24.900 align:middle line:84%
because we, ourselves,
in our lives,

00:05:24.900 --> 00:05:26.620 align:middle line:90%
went through this same process.

00:05:26.620 --> 00:05:28.570 align:middle line:84%
When we were young,
we were kind of

00:05:28.570 --> 00:05:32.260 align:middle line:84%
caught in the amorphous
thinking of teachers and family

00:05:32.260 --> 00:05:33.230 align:middle line:90%
and everything.

00:05:33.230 --> 00:05:36.010 align:middle line:84%
But as you mature, especially
when you hit your 20s,

00:05:36.010 --> 00:05:37.960 align:middle line:90%
you begin individuating.

00:05:37.960 --> 00:05:41.740 align:middle line:84%
You begin, I'm the best sax
player in the neighborhood.

00:05:41.740 --> 00:05:43.550 align:middle line:84%
I can do math
better than anybody.

00:05:43.550 --> 00:05:44.530 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Saxodelic.

00:05:44.530 --> 00:05:46.607 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Saxodelic.

00:05:46.607 --> 00:05:48.190 align:middle line:84%
So I think that's
another thing that's

00:05:48.190 --> 00:05:51.130 align:middle line:84%
going on here, another
reason why we like the film.

00:05:51.130 --> 00:05:53.720 align:middle line:84%
But in the end,
it is a nightmare.

00:05:53.720 --> 00:05:55.720 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: So what we're
going to see in this scene

00:05:55.720 --> 00:05:57.730 align:middle line:90%
is this imprinting protocol.

00:05:57.730 --> 00:06:00.670 align:middle line:84%
And I was able to mine a
lot of data out of this,

00:06:00.670 --> 00:06:02.930 align:middle line:90%
a lot of really esoteric topics.

00:06:02.930 --> 00:06:08.380 align:middle line:84%
So if we look to the imprinting
protocol, we'll see that.

00:06:08.380 --> 00:06:10.780 align:middle line:84%
So I read this scene
cabalistically,

00:06:10.780 --> 00:06:13.200 align:middle line:84%
and I know that, because
Spielberg often uses

00:06:13.200 --> 00:06:15.550 align:middle line:84%
the cabalistic
mystical tradition out

00:06:15.550 --> 00:06:16.510 align:middle line:90%
of medieval Judaism.

00:06:16.510 --> 00:06:19.480 align:middle line:84%
And what you have here
is a retelling, in a way,

00:06:19.480 --> 00:06:20.890 align:middle line:90%
of the Genesis narrative.

00:06:20.890 --> 00:06:25.510 align:middle line:84%
So God creates man in his image
and breathes life into him.

00:06:25.510 --> 00:06:27.550 align:middle line:84%
And we're told in Genesis
that that creation

00:06:27.550 --> 00:06:31.276 align:middle line:84%
is done through some form
of verbal sound vibration.

00:06:31.276 --> 00:06:32.650 align:middle line:84%
If you're familiar
with cymatics,

00:06:32.650 --> 00:06:36.931 align:middle line:84%
you get the idea of sound
imprinting its forms on nature.

00:06:36.931 --> 00:06:38.630 align:middle line:90%
>>Is it a game?

00:06:38.630 --> 00:06:39.430 align:middle line:90%
>>No.

00:06:39.430 --> 00:06:44.590 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to read some words,
and they won't make any sense,

00:06:44.590 --> 00:06:48.910 align:middle line:84%
but I want you to listen
to them anyway, and look

00:06:48.910 --> 00:06:50.890 align:middle line:90%
at me all the time.

00:06:50.890 --> 00:06:53.090 align:middle line:90%
Can you do that?

00:06:53.090 --> 00:06:54.160 align:middle line:90%
>>Yes, Monica.

00:06:54.160 --> 00:06:55.900 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: So in the same
way, these vowels,

00:06:55.900 --> 00:06:58.660 align:middle line:84%
these sounds that Monica makes,
as his mother, as his mother

00:06:58.660 --> 00:07:01.310 align:middle line:84%
archetype, is what
actually awakens him.

00:07:01.310 --> 00:07:03.939 align:middle line:84%
And she actually-- you'll
notice on that diagram

00:07:03.939 --> 00:07:04.980 align:middle line:90%
there were chakra points.

00:07:04.980 --> 00:07:06.771 align:middle line:84%
There was here and in
the back of his neck,

00:07:06.771 --> 00:07:09.370 align:middle line:84%
so you have these regions
or these zones that

00:07:09.370 --> 00:07:13.000 align:middle line:84%
are specific to the hermetic
tradition and so forth.

00:07:13.000 --> 00:07:16.600 align:middle line:84%
And so I read that as, like
you said, it is an awakening.

00:07:16.600 --> 00:07:19.810 align:middle line:84%
But it requires almost
a ritual process.

00:07:19.810 --> 00:07:23.440 align:middle line:84%
And so it's very strange
that we're seeing Mecha,

00:07:23.440 --> 00:07:25.000 align:middle line:84%
as they're called
in the film, set

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:27.110 align:middle line:90%
against the Orga, the humanity.

00:07:27.110 --> 00:07:29.950 align:middle line:84%
And so it's science, it's
scientism, it's technology,

00:07:29.950 --> 00:07:34.960 align:middle line:84%
but it still contains
that ritual magic aspect.

00:07:34.960 --> 00:07:35.930 align:middle line:90%
>>Hurricane.

00:07:35.930 --> 00:07:36.730 align:middle line:90%
Dolphin.

00:07:36.730 --> 00:07:39.922 align:middle line:90%


00:07:39.922 --> 00:07:40.722 align:middle line:90%
Tulip.

00:07:40.722 --> 00:07:44.270 align:middle line:90%


00:07:44.270 --> 00:07:45.070 align:middle line:90%
Monica.

00:07:45.070 --> 00:07:47.588 align:middle line:90%


00:07:47.588 --> 00:07:48.388 align:middle line:90%
David.

00:07:48.388 --> 00:07:50.910 align:middle line:90%


00:07:50.910 --> 00:07:51.710 align:middle line:90%
Monica.

00:07:51.710 --> 00:08:04.010 align:middle line:90%


00:08:04.010 --> 00:08:04.900 align:middle line:90%
All right.

00:08:04.900 --> 00:08:07.990 align:middle line:90%


00:08:07.990 --> 00:08:10.499 align:middle line:90%
I wonder if I did that right.

00:08:10.499 --> 00:08:12.764 align:middle line:90%
[INAUDIBLE]

00:08:12.764 --> 00:08:14.890 align:middle line:84%
>>What were those
words for, Mommy?

00:08:14.890 --> 00:08:19.830 align:middle line:90%


00:08:19.830 --> 00:08:23.782 align:middle line:90%
>>What did you call me?

00:08:23.782 --> 00:08:24.770 align:middle line:90%
>>Mommy.

00:08:24.770 --> 00:08:27.734 align:middle line:90%


00:08:27.734 --> 00:08:29.216 align:middle line:90%
>>Who am I, David?

00:08:29.216 --> 00:08:33.662 align:middle line:90%


00:08:33.662 --> 00:08:36.650 align:middle line:90%
>>You are my mommy.

00:08:36.650 --> 00:08:39.600 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: I think that
that's what David goes through

00:08:39.600 --> 00:08:42.440 align:middle line:84%
as he's searching for his
soul throughout the film,

00:08:42.440 --> 00:08:43.900 align:middle line:90%
and you're right.

00:08:43.900 --> 00:08:47.500 align:middle line:84%
She did ignite him
in a way with words,

00:08:47.500 --> 00:08:50.180 align:middle line:84%
and we don't really even
understand the words

00:08:50.180 --> 00:08:52.799 align:middle line:84%
that Spielberg is
even choosing here.

00:08:52.799 --> 00:08:55.340 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: Now another level that's
a little bit darker and more

00:08:55.340 --> 00:08:56.900 align:middle line:84%
nefarious, something
similar to what

00:08:56.900 --> 00:09:01.220 align:middle line:84%
we saw in "Blade Runner" is
this idea of there being layers

00:09:01.220 --> 00:09:03.710 align:middle line:84%
to consciousness and
that you could actually

00:09:03.710 --> 00:09:06.620 align:middle line:84%
tap into or control
how a person thinks

00:09:06.620 --> 00:09:10.610 align:middle line:84%
or their thought process and
maybe even implant new memories

00:09:10.610 --> 00:09:12.290 align:middle line:90%
or erase memories.

00:09:12.290 --> 00:09:14.550 align:middle line:84%
And this is done through,
for example, hypnosis.

00:09:14.550 --> 00:09:17.300 align:middle line:10%
So the CIA did a lot of
studies into hypnosis,

00:09:17.300 --> 00:09:19.730 align:middle line:10%
and Dr. George Estabrooks
wrote a famous essay

00:09:19.730 --> 00:09:21.850 align:middle line:10%
in "Science Digest"
back in 1971.

00:09:21.850 --> 00:09:23.890 align:middle line:84%
It's called "Hypnosis
Comes of Age,"

00:09:23.890 --> 00:09:27.530 align:middle line:84%
and he talks about how he could
create a military courier, who

00:09:27.530 --> 00:09:29.231 align:middle line:84%
could have alternate
personalities,

00:09:29.231 --> 00:09:30.980 align:middle line:84%
and then they could
send him on a mission.

00:09:30.980 --> 00:09:32.720 align:middle line:84%
And the only person
who could access

00:09:32.720 --> 00:09:35.060 align:middle line:84%
those memories suppressed
in an alternate personality

00:09:35.060 --> 00:09:38.190 align:middle line:84%
would be the person who had the
key codes or the trigger codes.

00:09:38.190 --> 00:09:41.540 align:middle line:84%
And so I read this as that,
in a way, relating to this,

00:09:41.540 --> 00:09:45.790 align:middle line:84%
because we're going to see Jude
Law's character is a sex bot.

00:09:45.790 --> 00:09:47.060 align:middle line:90%
He's a sex operative.

00:09:47.060 --> 00:09:48.800 align:middle line:84%
So yes, these are
bots, but you have

00:09:48.800 --> 00:09:50.930 align:middle line:84%
to understand that it
operates on multiple levels.

00:09:50.930 --> 00:09:55.310 align:middle line:84%
So these people are being used
in an allegorical way for how

00:09:55.310 --> 00:09:57.890 align:middle line:84%
the elite, how the establishment
uses people in Hollywood

00:09:57.890 --> 00:10:00.290 align:middle line:90%
and so forth as sex operatives.

00:10:00.290 --> 00:10:03.450 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: A lot of
this AI actually began

00:10:03.450 --> 00:10:07.250 align:middle line:84%
with those experiments in the
'50s and Jose Delgado stopping

00:10:07.250 --> 00:10:08.835 align:middle line:90%
the bull with electrodes.

00:10:08.835 --> 00:10:09.752 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Electrodes.

00:10:09.752 --> 00:10:11.210 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Yep,
and so these things

00:10:11.210 --> 00:10:12.501 align:middle line:90%
have been going on a long time.

00:10:12.501 --> 00:10:15.150 align:middle line:84%
And I know Spielberg has to
be really into these things,

00:10:15.150 --> 00:10:16.310 align:middle line:90%
because we all are.

00:10:16.310 --> 00:10:18.140 align:middle line:90%
And you're right.

00:10:18.140 --> 00:10:20.330 align:middle line:84%
The trigger words
can do anything,

00:10:20.330 --> 00:10:24.470 align:middle line:84%
and I mean the robots can
be controlled from without.

00:10:24.470 --> 00:10:27.140 align:middle line:90%
They could be hacked.

00:10:27.140 --> 00:10:29.025 align:middle line:84%
Whoever's in control
is in control of them.

00:10:29.025 --> 00:10:30.900 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: And from that
technocratic world view

00:10:30.900 --> 00:10:32.274 align:middle line:84%
or that technocratic
perspective,

00:10:32.274 --> 00:10:34.980 align:middle line:84%
they view everything in a
naturalistic reductionist

00:10:34.980 --> 00:10:35.780 align:middle line:90%
perspective.

00:10:35.780 --> 00:10:37.340 align:middle line:90%
So everything is material.

00:10:37.340 --> 00:10:40.010 align:middle line:84%
Everything is essentially a
giant program that's running,

00:10:40.010 --> 00:10:42.200 align:middle line:84%
and so really, programming
a bot or programming

00:10:42.200 --> 00:10:45.090 align:middle line:84%
a human is no different,
because they view us as bots.

00:10:45.090 --> 00:10:45.890 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: They do.

00:10:45.890 --> 00:10:46.970 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Biological bots.

00:10:46.970 --> 00:10:47.770 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: They do.

00:10:47.770 --> 00:10:50.490 align:middle line:84%
And they very much
view us that way.

00:10:50.490 --> 00:10:54.320 align:middle line:84%
And you know, it goes back
to "The Republic" by Plato,

00:10:54.320 --> 00:10:55.120 align:middle line:90%
where he's just--

00:10:55.120 --> 00:10:55.953 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Cybernetics.

00:10:55.953 --> 00:10:58.442 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah, he's
designing this perfect society,

00:10:58.442 --> 00:10:59.900 align:middle line:84%
and one of the
things that can't be

00:10:59.900 --> 00:11:03.920 align:middle line:84%
allowed in this perfect society
is any kind of individualism.

00:11:03.920 --> 00:11:06.350 align:middle line:84%
It has to be driven out, and
you can't think for yourself,

00:11:06.350 --> 00:11:08.060 align:middle line:90%
because that would be dangerous.

00:11:08.060 --> 00:11:11.220 align:middle line:84%
And again, we get back to
those same themes here,

00:11:11.220 --> 00:11:15.200 align:middle line:84%
and the relationships between
Platonism and socialism

00:11:15.200 --> 00:11:16.970 align:middle line:90%
are very close to each other.

00:11:16.970 --> 00:11:18.980 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of the
socialist countries

00:11:18.980 --> 00:11:21.050 align:middle line:84%
are very controlling
of how you think.

00:11:21.050 --> 00:11:23.530 align:middle line:84%
That is the definition
of Stalinism,

00:11:23.530 --> 00:11:25.595 align:middle line:90%
is political thought control.

00:11:25.595 --> 00:11:27.470 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: And actually,
what we're going to see

00:11:27.470 --> 00:11:29.732 align:middle line:84%
is that Plato
talked about the way

00:11:29.732 --> 00:11:31.940 align:middle line:84%
that you could control the
masses through their baser

00:11:31.940 --> 00:11:32.870 align:middle line:90%
desires.

00:11:32.870 --> 00:11:35.450 align:middle line:84%
But when we looked to the scene
about the flesh fair, what

00:11:35.450 --> 00:11:39.080 align:middle line:84%
we're going to see is man's
baser desires, that temptation

00:11:39.080 --> 00:11:41.454 align:middle line:84%
to lust and to
violence, being a means

00:11:41.454 --> 00:11:42.620 align:middle line:90%
by which they're controlled.

00:11:42.620 --> 00:11:44.886 align:middle line:84%
And so it's a very, as I
said, a Dante-esque scene.

00:11:44.886 --> 00:11:46.010 align:middle line:90%
It's just like the inferno.

00:11:46.010 --> 00:11:46.810 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Very.

00:11:46.810 --> 00:11:47.660 align:middle line:90%
Very much.

00:11:47.660 --> 00:11:49.076 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: But what's
going to happen

00:11:49.076 --> 00:11:51.320 align:middle line:84%
is it's going to show that
contrast between the Orga

00:11:51.320 --> 00:11:55.460 align:middle line:84%
and the Mecha, how the Orga
are captive to their desires.

00:11:55.460 --> 00:11:57.440 align:middle line:84%
And the reason that
it's, I believe,

00:11:57.440 --> 00:11:59.610 align:middle line:84%
a transhumanist fairytale
is that Spielberg

00:11:59.610 --> 00:12:02.104 align:middle line:84%
is going to constantly
present the bots as superior.

00:12:02.104 --> 00:12:03.020 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Absolutely.

00:12:03.020 --> 00:12:04.894 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: And so if we
look at this scene here,

00:12:04.894 --> 00:12:06.900 align:middle line:90%
we'll see that.

00:12:06.900 --> 00:12:08.400 align:middle line:84%
>>What are you going
to do with him?

00:12:08.400 --> 00:12:10.610 align:middle line:90%
>>Put him where he belongs--

00:12:10.610 --> 00:12:12.640 align:middle line:90%
in show business.

00:12:12.640 --> 00:12:15.740 align:middle line:84%
>>It was certainly my good
fortune running into you.

00:12:15.740 --> 00:12:19.340 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: Gladitorial
events, dehumanization.

00:12:19.340 --> 00:12:22.130 align:middle line:84%
That's what I see this as,
but it's, again, the reversal.

00:12:22.130 --> 00:12:24.140 align:middle line:84%
It's the humans that
are de-humanized,

00:12:24.140 --> 00:12:27.640 align:middle line:84%
because they're like
the pagans in Rome, who

00:12:27.640 --> 00:12:30.590 align:middle line:84%
wanted to have these
giant gladiatorial events

00:12:30.590 --> 00:12:33.680 align:middle line:84%
and torture people and see them
eaten by lions and so forth.

00:12:33.680 --> 00:12:38.630 align:middle line:84%
But here, David and Jude Law are
almost our new savior figures.

00:12:38.630 --> 00:12:42.290 align:middle line:84%
They're kind of-- they're the
beginnings of a new humanity is

00:12:42.290 --> 00:12:43.880 align:middle line:90%
where this is going to take us.

00:12:43.880 --> 00:12:45.711 align:middle line:84%
But in Spielberg's
view, it's evolution,

00:12:45.711 --> 00:12:47.210 align:middle line:84%
so it's not really
humanity anymore.

00:12:47.210 --> 00:12:48.620 align:middle line:90%
We're post-human.

00:12:48.620 --> 00:12:51.616 align:middle line:84%
David is going to be the
founder of a new race,

00:12:51.616 --> 00:12:52.490 align:middle line:90%
we're going to learn.

00:12:52.490 --> 00:12:55.820 align:middle line:84%
They're aliens, but they're
mechanized robotic aliens,

00:12:55.820 --> 00:12:57.800 align:middle line:90%
which is a very weird turn.

00:12:57.800 --> 00:12:59.490 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah, hybrids almost.

00:12:59.490 --> 00:13:02.690 align:middle line:84%
And he goes out of his way to
make them look like aliens,

00:13:02.690 --> 00:13:05.660 align:middle line:84%
but if you're listening and
watching the movie intently,

00:13:05.660 --> 00:13:08.270 align:middle line:84%
you'll notice that they're
actually a more advanced

00:13:08.270 --> 00:13:10.636 align:middle line:90%
evolutionary form of David.

00:13:10.636 --> 00:13:16.330 align:middle line:84%
>>Ladies and gentlemen, boys and
girls and children of all ages,

00:13:16.330 --> 00:13:19.420 align:middle line:90%
what will they think of next?

00:13:19.420 --> 00:13:26.400 align:middle line:84%
See here a bitty bot, a
tinker toy, a living doll.

00:13:26.400 --> 00:13:28.700 align:middle line:84%
Of course, we all know
why they made him--

00:13:28.700 --> 00:13:33.230 align:middle line:84%
to speed your hearts, to
replace your children.

00:13:33.230 --> 00:13:35.030 align:middle line:84%
This is the latest
iteration in a series

00:13:35.030 --> 00:13:37.050 align:middle line:90%
of insults to human dignity.

00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:38.900 align:middle line:84%
>>And in the grand
scheme to phase out

00:13:38.900 --> 00:13:41.790 align:middle line:90%
all of God's little children.

00:13:41.790 --> 00:13:46.520 align:middle line:84%
>>Meet the next generation of
child designed to do just that.

00:13:46.520 --> 00:13:53.150 align:middle line:90%


00:13:53.150 --> 00:14:00.160 align:middle line:84%
Do not be fooled by the
artistry of this creation.

00:14:00.160 --> 00:14:04.170 align:middle line:84%
No doubt, there was talent in
the crafting of this simulator,

00:14:04.170 --> 00:14:06.890 align:middle line:84%
yet for the very
first strike, you

00:14:06.890 --> 00:14:12.265 align:middle line:84%
will see the biggest lie come
apart before your very eyes.

00:14:12.265 --> 00:14:13.259 align:middle line:90%
>>Don't burn me!

00:14:13.259 --> 00:14:15.247 align:middle line:90%
Don't burn me!

00:14:15.247 --> 00:14:17.235 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to
[INAUDIBLE] you!

00:14:17.235 --> 00:14:18.229 align:middle line:90%
Don't make me die.

00:14:18.229 --> 00:14:19.223 align:middle line:90%
I'm David.

00:14:19.223 --> 00:14:20.730 align:middle line:90%
I'm David.

00:14:20.730 --> 00:14:24.480 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: So there's a scene
earlier in the film that really

00:14:24.480 --> 00:14:28.890 align:middle line:84%
comes to fruition in the flesh
fair scene, where David is set

00:14:28.890 --> 00:14:31.110 align:middle line:84%
up against his brother,
who's a human, who

00:14:31.110 --> 00:14:35.419 align:middle line:84%
has like a wheelchair and
all this elaborate apparatus,

00:14:35.419 --> 00:14:37.710 align:middle line:84%
because he can't get around,
because he's got something

00:14:37.710 --> 00:14:38.793 align:middle line:90%
wrong with him, basically.

00:14:38.793 --> 00:14:40.530 align:middle line:90%
And the guy is a total butthole.

00:14:40.530 --> 00:14:41.750 align:middle line:90%
He's awful.

00:14:41.750 --> 00:14:44.070 align:middle line:84%
And so he actually
torments David.

00:14:44.070 --> 00:14:46.770 align:middle line:84%
David is totally
cool, really nice

00:14:46.770 --> 00:14:49.937 align:middle line:90%
to this rival kid, his brother.

00:14:49.937 --> 00:14:52.020 align:middle line:84%
So we almost have this
Cain and Abel kind of story

00:14:52.020 --> 00:14:53.490 align:middle line:90%
that's being retold.

00:14:53.490 --> 00:14:57.770 align:middle line:84%
We're getting the picture that
humans are basically the pits.

00:14:57.770 --> 00:15:01.020 align:middle line:84%
And then Monica has a
little bit of humanity,

00:15:01.020 --> 00:15:04.410 align:middle line:84%
but she actually forfeits that,
because she just lets David--

00:15:04.410 --> 00:15:06.750 align:middle line:84%
like she leaves him,
just abandons him out in

00:15:06.750 --> 00:15:07.620 align:middle line:90%
the wilderness.

00:15:07.620 --> 00:15:10.620 align:middle line:84%
And then he ends up
in the flesh fair,

00:15:10.620 --> 00:15:13.830 align:middle line:84%
and we see this total contrast
between David and Jude Law.

00:15:13.830 --> 00:15:16.590 align:middle line:84%
Jude Law is a sex
operative, a sex bot.

00:15:16.590 --> 00:15:18.420 align:middle line:84%
He doesn't understand
what's going on here.

00:15:18.420 --> 00:15:20.100 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't make sense to him.

00:15:20.100 --> 00:15:21.570 align:middle line:84%
And then we have
this giant crowd

00:15:21.570 --> 00:15:23.640 align:middle line:84%
of people who are
motivated and manipulated

00:15:23.640 --> 00:15:26.322 align:middle line:84%
by their baser
desires, base emotions,

00:15:26.322 --> 00:15:27.780 align:middle line:84%
and they want to
torture, they want

00:15:27.780 --> 00:15:31.100 align:middle line:84%
to destroy these bots,
who have been humanized.

00:15:31.100 --> 00:15:33.120 align:middle line:84%
But when they finally
see that it's a child,

00:15:33.120 --> 00:15:35.880 align:middle line:84%
and they mistakenly think
that David is a kid,

00:15:35.880 --> 00:15:37.971 align:middle line:90%
because he says, "Don't burn me.

00:15:37.971 --> 00:15:40.740 align:middle line:84%
Don't burn me," they get
mad at Brendan Gleeson,

00:15:40.740 --> 00:15:42.680 align:middle line:84%
and they throw the
bean bags at him.

00:15:42.680 --> 00:15:44.535 align:middle line:84%
So what do you think
about that contrast?

00:15:44.535 --> 00:15:48.000 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Well, I think that's
exactly what the movie's about.

00:15:48.000 --> 00:15:50.850 align:middle line:84%
And also, when his
brother tortures him,

00:15:50.850 --> 00:15:52.290 align:middle line:84%
the final torture
is throwing him

00:15:52.290 --> 00:15:56.356 align:middle line:84%
into the pool, which is
where David ends up later.

00:15:56.356 --> 00:15:57.480 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Foreshadows, right?

00:15:57.480 --> 00:15:59.521 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Exactly, which
is all done by, really,

00:15:59.521 --> 00:16:00.550 align:middle line:90%
the cruelty of humans.

00:16:00.550 --> 00:16:01.350 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Yes.

00:16:01.350 --> 00:16:03.270 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: And so we
see this water motif

00:16:03.270 --> 00:16:05.370 align:middle line:84%
going through the
film also, where

00:16:05.370 --> 00:16:07.950 align:middle line:84%
the more that David
interacts with water,

00:16:07.950 --> 00:16:10.570 align:middle line:84%
the more his consciousness
seems to rise.

00:16:10.570 --> 00:16:14.086 align:middle line:84%
And we know that water is
symbolic for consciousness

00:16:14.086 --> 00:16:15.210 align:middle line:90%
in the esoteric traditions.

00:16:15.210 --> 00:16:18.810 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: Now, on that
point, even Dr. Allen Hobby

00:16:18.810 --> 00:16:20.380 align:middle line:90%
is kind of a butt.

00:16:20.380 --> 00:16:21.640 align:middle line:90%
He is not a great guy.

00:16:21.640 --> 00:16:23.139 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: No, he's
not, not at all.

00:16:23.139 --> 00:16:24.612 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: And David
gets back to him,

00:16:24.612 --> 00:16:27.070 align:middle line:84%
and Dr. Hobby basically doesn't
care what happens to David.

00:16:27.070 --> 00:16:28.480 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Does not care at all.

00:16:28.480 --> 00:16:30.225 align:middle line:84%
In fact, no humans
care about him at all.

00:16:30.225 --> 00:16:31.025 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Exactly.

00:16:31.025 --> 00:16:33.270 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Except for his
mom at the very beginning.

00:16:33.270 --> 00:16:37.890 align:middle line:84%
And even in the ending, where
the robot people in the future

00:16:37.890 --> 00:16:41.610 align:middle line:84%
bring her back for one day,
and typical Spielberg trying

00:16:41.610 --> 00:16:43.650 align:middle line:84%
to find a happy
ending in this thing,

00:16:43.650 --> 00:16:48.300 align:middle line:84%
even that, she's kind of odd
and strange and alienated,

00:16:48.300 --> 00:16:50.540 align:middle line:90%
and it's a very--

00:16:50.540 --> 00:16:53.010 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: She's a holographic
recreation of a memory,

00:16:53.010 --> 00:16:55.990 align:middle line:84%
and she's just as vacant
as she was in real life.

00:16:55.990 --> 00:16:56.790 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Exactly.

00:16:56.790 --> 00:16:59.670 align:middle line:84%
And that's what they're
trying to say here.

00:16:59.670 --> 00:17:01.380 align:middle line:90%
Human beings are not that great.

00:17:01.380 --> 00:17:05.680 align:middle line:84%
They almost deserve to get it,
and the robots are superior.

00:17:05.680 --> 00:17:06.480 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Right.

00:17:06.480 --> 00:17:09.569 align:middle line:84%
So if we think, though, back
to that theme of everything

00:17:09.569 --> 00:17:12.569 align:middle line:84%
being programmed and
mechanized, and what

00:17:12.569 --> 00:17:14.910 align:middle line:84%
we've noticed in the character
of David, as you said,

00:17:14.910 --> 00:17:18.300 align:middle line:84%
is that he's achieved
self-actualization and free

00:17:18.300 --> 00:17:20.799 align:middle line:84%
association, free thought,
free will, basically.

00:17:20.799 --> 00:17:21.599 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Exactly.

00:17:21.599 --> 00:17:23.700 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: But the rest of
the people in the story--

00:17:23.700 --> 00:17:25.074 align:middle line:84%
even Jude Law--
they don't really

00:17:25.074 --> 00:17:26.280 align:middle line:90%
seem to have this free will.

00:17:26.280 --> 00:17:27.720 align:middle line:90%
They're all programmed.

00:17:27.720 --> 00:17:31.350 align:middle line:84%
And that's why Dr. No
is going to tell David

00:17:31.350 --> 00:17:34.080 align:middle line:84%
that everything that
he's looking for,

00:17:34.080 --> 00:17:37.470 align:middle line:84%
he can't answer his question,
because it's a flat fact.

00:17:37.470 --> 00:17:39.900 align:middle line:84%
And what David is trying
to do is associate things

00:17:39.900 --> 00:17:42.270 align:middle line:84%
through archetypes
and through free will

00:17:42.270 --> 00:17:44.040 align:middle line:90%
and through creativity.

00:17:44.040 --> 00:17:45.840 align:middle line:84%
And the robot that
he's talking to-- it's

00:17:45.840 --> 00:17:48.120 align:middle line:84%
a bot talking to a bot--
doesn't have that ability,

00:17:48.120 --> 00:17:51.910 align:middle line:84%
so this is why David is
going to be the future is

00:17:51.910 --> 00:17:53.310 align:middle line:90%
because he's not just a bot.

00:17:53.310 --> 00:17:55.270 align:middle line:84%
He's a bot with free
will and creativity.

00:17:55.270 --> 00:17:56.520 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: That is exactly it.

00:17:56.520 --> 00:17:58.395 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: And we see that
in the "Dr. No" clip.

00:17:58.395 --> 00:18:00.412 align:middle line:90%
>>What if a fairy tale is real?

00:18:00.412 --> 00:18:05.924 align:middle line:84%
Then wouldn't it be
fact, a flat fact?

00:18:05.924 --> 00:18:06.820 align:middle line:90%
>>Say no more.

00:18:06.820 --> 00:18:10.800 align:middle line:90%


00:18:10.800 --> 00:18:14.580 align:middle line:90%
New category, please.

00:18:14.580 --> 00:18:25.470 align:middle line:90%
Combine fact with fairy tale.

00:18:25.470 --> 00:18:30.926 align:middle line:90%


00:18:30.926 --> 00:18:33.690 align:middle line:90%
Now, ask him again.

00:18:33.690 --> 00:18:43.140 align:middle line:90%


00:18:43.140 --> 00:18:59.040 align:middle line:84%
>>How can the blue fairy make
a robot into a real live boy?

00:18:59.040 --> 00:19:03.000 align:middle line:90%
[BUZZING]

00:19:03.000 --> 00:19:07.280 align:middle line:84%
>>Come away, oh, human child
to the waters and the wild,

00:19:07.280 --> 00:19:09.880 align:middle line:84%
with a fairy hand in
hand, for the world's

00:19:09.880 --> 00:19:13.280 align:middle line:84%
more full of weeping
than you can understand.

00:19:13.280 --> 00:19:17.620 align:middle line:84%
Your quest will be perilous,
yet the reward is beyond price.

00:19:17.620 --> 00:19:20.950 align:middle line:84%
In his book, "How Can
a Robot Become Human,"

00:19:20.950 --> 00:19:23.170 align:middle line:84%
Professor Allen Hobby
writes of the power which

00:19:23.170 --> 00:19:26.650 align:middle line:90%
will transform Mecha into Orga.

00:19:26.650 --> 00:19:28.600 align:middle line:84%
>>Will you tell me
how to find her?

00:19:28.600 --> 00:19:31.480 align:middle line:90%
>>Discovery is quite possible.

00:19:31.480 --> 00:19:36.340 align:middle line:84%
Our blue fairy does exist in
