basically, a Pinocchio

00:21:50.580 --> 00:21:52.240 align:middle line:90%
setting, the blue fairy.

00:21:52.240 --> 00:21:55.500 align:middle line:84%
And he's frozen there for
millennia or eons, basically.

00:21:55.500 --> 00:21:56.790 align:middle line:90%
We don't know how long.

00:21:56.790 --> 00:21:59.610 align:middle line:84%
What's weird about that is
that it's very similar, again,

00:21:59.610 --> 00:22:02.970 align:middle line:84%
to "Dante's Inferno," because
at the pit, the very bottom

00:22:02.970 --> 00:22:04.620 align:middle line:90%
of hell, it's frozen.

00:22:04.620 --> 00:22:05.880 align:middle line:90%
It's not lava.

00:22:05.880 --> 00:22:07.470 align:middle line:90%
It's not a pit of fire.

00:22:07.470 --> 00:22:09.940 align:middle line:84%
It's the devil,
basically, frozen in ice.

00:22:09.940 --> 00:22:10.740 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:22:10.740 --> 00:22:14.250 align:middle line:84%
So I'm not saying that David
is necessarily the devil,

00:22:14.250 --> 00:22:16.500 align:middle line:84%
but he's an anti-hero
in a way, because he's

00:22:16.500 --> 00:22:18.450 align:middle line:90%
frozen there for eons.

00:22:18.450 --> 00:22:23.311 align:middle line:84%
He's then awakened by his
progeny, who, as we said,

00:22:23.311 --> 00:22:24.810 align:middle line:84%
eventually evolved
from him somehow.

00:22:24.810 --> 00:22:25.980 align:middle line:90%
We don't know how.

00:22:25.980 --> 00:22:28.320 align:middle line:90%
But it's AI aliens, basically.

00:22:28.320 --> 00:22:32.070 align:middle line:84%
So "AI", I see it, as
I said, as a combining

00:22:32.070 --> 00:22:34.950 align:middle line:84%
of a whole bunch of
fairy tales and mythology

00:22:34.950 --> 00:22:39.240 align:middle line:84%
and meshing it with something
seemingly impossible

00:22:39.240 --> 00:22:42.660 align:middle line:84%
to mesh with science
and technology.

00:22:42.660 --> 00:22:47.550 align:middle line:84%
The flat fact and the fairy tale
seem totally incommensurable,

00:22:47.550 --> 00:22:50.020 align:middle line:84%
but he's meshed them together
in a very fascinating,

00:22:50.020 --> 00:22:50.820 align:middle line:90%
interesting way.

00:22:50.820 --> 00:22:54.600 align:middle line:84%
I don't like, necessarily,
the way the film ends.

00:22:54.600 --> 00:22:56.842 align:middle line:84%
But it is, basically, a
transhumanist fairy tale.

00:22:56.842 --> 00:22:58.800 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Well, I think
it's very interesting,

00:22:58.800 --> 00:23:00.900 align:middle line:84%
because the next film
that we're going to watch,

00:23:00.900 --> 00:23:04.320 align:middle line:84%
"Minority Report," which
came out a year later,

00:23:04.320 --> 00:23:08.590 align:middle line:84%
it has an ending very similar
to the ending of "AI,"

00:23:08.590 --> 00:23:12.450 align:middle line:84%
in that Spielberg is
weaving this fantasy in kind

00:23:12.450 --> 00:23:15.480 align:middle line:84%
of an attempt to have a
happy ending, no matter what.

00:23:15.480 --> 00:23:16.800 align:middle line:90%
So that will be interesting.

