eliminated, we're told.

00:24:57.870 --> 00:25:00.890 align:middle line:84%
And this is done through
this advanced technology that

00:25:00.890 --> 00:25:04.580 align:middle line:84%
also uses precogs or people
who have premonitions

00:25:04.580 --> 00:25:05.730 align:middle line:90%
of the future.

00:25:05.730 --> 00:25:07.700 align:middle line:84%
So I think Spielberg
is, once again,

00:25:07.700 --> 00:25:10.460 align:middle line:84%
meshing the fairy
tale or the religious

00:25:10.460 --> 00:25:14.120 align:middle line:84%
or the metaphysical with
science and technology

00:25:14.120 --> 00:25:16.757 align:middle line:84%
in this weird dystopia that's,
again, from Philip K Dick.

00:25:16.757 --> 00:25:18.590 align:middle line:84%
And the reason Philip
K Dick is so important

00:25:18.590 --> 00:25:20.630 align:middle line:84%
is that, as we said,
he was hanging out

00:25:20.630 --> 00:25:22.530 align:middle line:90%
with the Silicon Valley elite.

00:25:22.530 --> 00:25:25.220 align:middle line:84%
He was writing about the
internet back in "Ubik,"

00:25:25.220 --> 00:25:27.770 align:middle line:84%
decades ago before
the internet came out.

00:25:27.770 --> 00:25:30.230 align:middle line:84%
And so in all of these
stories that Dick is writing,

00:25:30.230 --> 00:25:33.390 align:middle line:84%
he's presaging a dark
dystopian future.

00:25:33.390 --> 00:25:35.510 align:middle line:84%
And in "Minority Report,"
it's, once again,

00:25:35.510 --> 00:25:39.560 align:middle line:84%
this blending of the
religious into technocracy.

00:25:39.560 --> 00:25:41.460 align:middle line:90%
So it's called the temple.

00:25:41.460 --> 00:25:45.290 align:middle line:84%
The temple is what houses this
almost trinitarian idea here

00:25:45.290 --> 00:25:49.490 align:middle line:84%
of these three precognizant
individuals, who are predicting

00:25:49.490 --> 00:25:51.340 align:middle line:90%
where crimes are going to be.

00:25:51.340 --> 00:25:54.890 align:middle line:84%
