00:28:33.254 --> 00:28:35.420 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: That was a great
scene, one of the best--

00:28:35.420 --> 00:28:35.720 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Yeah.

00:28:35.720 --> 00:28:37.960 align:middle line:84%
You see the retinal
scanning, and you see this.

00:28:37.960 --> 00:28:40.590 align:middle line:10%
And again, I can't
stress how ominous

00:28:40.590 --> 00:28:44.570 align:middle line:10%
it is when I see the CEO of IBM
giving public lectures about

00:28:44.570 --> 00:28:47.097 align:middle line:10%
the future smart cities
like Rio and Singapore,

00:28:47.097 --> 00:28:48.680 align:middle line:10%
and she says,
basically, there's going

00:28:48.680 --> 00:28:51.740 align:middle line:10%
to be a giant AI
central grid hub,

00:28:51.740 --> 00:28:54.680 align:middle line:10%
and the entire city will
be wired and linked in,

00:28:54.680 --> 00:28:55.936 align:middle line:10%
an internet of things.

00:28:55.936 --> 00:28:57.560 align:middle line:84%
And everything will
be known about you.

00:28:57.560 --> 00:28:59.000 align:middle line:84%
And so it's going
to be so great,

00:28:59.000 --> 00:29:01.070 align:middle line:84%
because when you walk
into the 7-Eleven,

00:29:01.070 --> 00:29:02.610 align:middle line:90%
they're going to know which--

00:29:02.610 --> 00:29:04.627 align:middle line:84%
that you like the
Flaming Cheetos

00:29:04.627 --> 00:29:06.710 align:middle line:84%
and that you want the
Nutter Butters, because they

00:29:06.710 --> 00:29:08.390 align:middle line:90%
know what you like.

00:29:08.390 --> 00:29:09.600 align:middle line:90%
So it's going to be great.

00:29:09.600 --> 00:29:10.895 align:middle line:90%
It's going to be phenomenal.

00:29:10.895 --> 00:29:12.770 align:middle line:84%
And there won't be any
crime, because they're

00:29:12.770 --> 00:29:15.187 align:middle line:84%
going to know ahead of-- now,
that sounds like a huge scam

00:29:15.187 --> 00:29:15.986 align:middle line:90%
to me.

00:29:15.986 --> 00:29:17.450 align:middle line:84%
I mean, how are
you going to know?

00:29:17.450 --> 00:29:20.930 align:middle line:84%
And what's neat about this film
is that it shows it's a scam.

00:29:20.930 --> 00:29:21.750 align:middle line:90%
The whole--

00:29:21.750 --> 00:29:22.750 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: It is a scam.

00:29:22.750 --> 00:29:24.950 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: The whole precog
system that's set up

00:29:24.950 --> 00:29:26.597 align:middle line:90%
is run by a total crook.

00:29:26.597 --> 00:29:28.430 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: And I think
that's what Spielberg

00:29:28.430 --> 00:29:30.484 align:middle line:84%
is trying to warn
us about here, is

00:29:30.484 --> 00:29:32.900 align:middle line:84%
that we'll have no civil rights
when the technocrats build

00:29:32.900 --> 00:29:33.800 align:middle line:90%
their world.

00:29:33.800 --> 00:29:35.880 align:middle line:84%
And they don't-- again,
they're out of control.

00:29:35.880 --> 00:29:39.200 align:middle line:84%
There's nobody watching what
IBM and Google are doing.

00:29:39.200 --> 00:29:42.290 align:middle line:84%
No government agencies coming in
and looking around and saying,

00:29:42.290 --> 00:29:45.420 align:middle line:84%
hey, what-- is this really
what you want to be doing here?

00:29:45.420 --> 00:29:47.390 align:middle line:90%
And so there's no governance.

00:29:47.390 --> 00:29:50.270 align:middle line:84%
It's wild west, and
where they're headed,

00:29:50.270 --> 00:29:51.240 align:middle line:90%
we don't even know.

00:29:51.240 --> 00:29:55.160 align:middle line:84%
I've been told by insiders
that they're 40, 50 years ahead

00:29:55.160 --> 00:29:58.130 align:middle line:84%
of us at DARPA, and
whatever that means.

00:29:58.130 --> 00:30:01.520 align:middle line:84%
I have no idea what 50
years from us in the future

00:30:01.520 --> 00:30:02.970 align:middle line:90%
what we're going to have.

00:30:02.970 --> 00:30:05.810 align:middle line:84%
But I can imagine, and I
think Spielberg is giving us

00:30:05.810 --> 00:30:07.959 align:middle line:84%
a real great display
of what we're

00:30:07.959 --> 00:30:10.250 align:middle line:84%
going to have to deal with
when we walk into department

00:30:10.250 --> 00:30:12.064 align:middle line:90%
stores in the very near future.

00:30:12.064 --> 00:30:14.480 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: It makes me think of
the voice to skull technology

00:30:14.480 --> 00:30:17.070 align:middle line:84%
that DARPA developed back
even in the '80s and '90s,

00:30:17.070 --> 00:30:20.859 align:middle line:84%
where they could actually target
your skull to hear that you

00:30:20.859 --> 00:30:21.900 align:middle line:90%
need the Flaming Cheetos.

00:30:21.900 --> 00:30:23.891 align:middle line:84%
Or nobody else is hearing
this, and then people

00:30:23.891 --> 00:30:25.890 align:middle line:84%
are thinking you're crazy,
because you're here--

00:30:25.890 --> 00:30:26.690 align:middle line:90%
I'm hearing voices.

00:30:26.690 --> 00:30:27.939 align:middle line:90%
And what are they telling you?

00:30:27.939 --> 00:30:28.820 align:middle line:90%
To buy the Cheetos.

00:30:28.820 --> 00:30:31.028 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Which is probably
what most channeling is,

00:30:31.028 --> 00:30:32.770 align:middle line:84%
is the CIA getting
in somebody's head.

00:30:32.770 --> 00:30:33.830 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: That's true.

00:30:33.830 --> 00:30:35.375 align:middle line:84%
Like "Real Genius," If
you've seen that movie.

00:30:35.375 --> 00:30:35.750 align:middle line:90%
That's what they do.

00:30:35.750 --> 00:30:36.080 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Oh, yeah.

00:30:36.080 --> 00:30:37.205 align:middle line:90%
Great movie, "Real Genius."

00:30:37.205 --> 00:30:39.500 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: But so another
interesting aspect to this film

00:30:39.500 --> 00:30:41.190 align:middle line:90%
is drones.

00:30:41.190 --> 00:30:43.520 align:middle line:84%
Nobody really knew,
unless you were maybe

00:30:43.520 --> 00:30:45.290 align:middle line:84%
working at the Air
Force, that there

00:30:45.290 --> 00:30:49.650 align:middle line:84%
was going to be this big,
huge ordeal of drone warfare.

00:30:49.650 --> 00:30:50.765 align:middle line:90%
And now, it's commonplace.

00:30:50.765 --> 00:30:52.306 align:middle line:84%
Oh, yeah, the drones,
and we're going

00:30:52.306 --> 00:30:55.970 align:middle line:84%
to drone attack all these Middle
Eastern countries and so forth.

00:30:55.970 --> 00:30:58.860 align:middle line:84%
But nobody knew about
drones, really, in 2002.

00:30:58.860 --> 00:31:01.520 align:middle line:84%
And so we're going to see that,
again, predicted in this clip.

00:31:01.520 --> 00:31:04.240 align:middle line:90%


00:31:04.240 --> 00:31:07.860 align:middle line:84%
So just as we see
in "Blade Runner,"

00:31:07.860 --> 00:31:10.000 align:middle line:84%
there's the focus on
eyes and eye world,

00:31:10.000 --> 00:31:12.460 align:middle line:84%
because it's a unique
signature for who you are,

00:31:12.460 --> 00:31:14.110 align:middle line:90%
your identity, retinal scanning.

00:31:14.110 --> 00:31:17.020 align:middle line:84%
And so in this dystopia, once
again from Philip K Dick, just

00:31:17.020 --> 00:31:19.620 align:middle line:84%
like "Blade Runner,"
he's concerned with eyes.

00:31:19.620 --> 00:31:22.690 align:middle line:84%
And you have to get your eyes
replaced in this dystopia,

00:31:22.690 --> 00:31:24.850 align:middle line:84%
if you want to bypass
the jack-booted thugs who

00:31:24.850 --> 00:31:25.960 align:middle line:90%
are coming for you.

00:31:25.960 --> 00:31:26.960 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: That's right.

00:31:26.960 --> 00:31:30.010 align:middle line:84%
And also, Tom Cruise's
character's wife

00:31:30.010 --> 00:31:32.359 align:middle line:90%
uses an eye to get into the--

00:31:32.359 --> 00:31:33.400 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Oh, that's right.

00:31:33.400 --> 00:31:35.670 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: --to the
jail to free him.

00:31:35.670 --> 00:31:38.265 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, the eyes are a
big thing in this movie.

00:31:38.265 --> 00:31:39.598 align:middle line:90%
>>They're crying their eyes out.

00:31:39.598 --> 00:31:41.090 align:middle line:90%
They're terrified.

00:31:41.090 --> 00:31:41.790 align:middle line:84%
They're absolutely
terrified right now.

00:31:41.790 --> 00:31:43.485 align:middle line:84%
>>You don't want your kids to
know terror, keep them away

00:31:43.485 --> 00:31:44.714 align:middle line:90%
from me.

00:31:44.714 --> 00:31:48.650 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:31:48.650 --> 00:31:53.078 align:middle line:90%


00:31:53.078 --> 00:31:57.014 align:middle line:90%
[BUZZING]

00:31:57.014 --> 00:31:59.120 align:middle line:90%


00:31:59.120 --> 00:31:59.920 align:middle line:90%
>>Wait a minute.

00:31:59.920 --> 00:32:01.452 align:middle line:90%
The big cat's back.

00:32:01.452 --> 00:32:02.410 align:middle line:90%
What do you guys think?

00:32:02.410 --> 00:32:03.980 align:middle line:90%
A drunk, maybe can't wake up?

00:32:03.980 --> 00:32:06.172 align:middle line:84%
>>Yeah, some guy who
doesn't want to get read.

00:32:06.172 --> 00:32:09.170 align:middle line:84%
Folks, please, be quiet,
and close your doors.

00:32:09.170 --> 00:32:10.170 align:middle line:90%
Go back inside.

00:32:10.170 --> 00:32:20.170 align:middle line:90%


00:32:20.170 --> 00:32:23.046 align:middle line:90%
Be quiet, and close the door.

00:32:23.046 --> 00:32:26.504 align:middle line:90%
>>[GROANS]

00:32:26.504 --> 00:32:29.468 align:middle line:90%


00:32:29.468 --> 00:32:30.456 align:middle line:90%
>>We got an ID.

00:32:30.456 --> 00:32:33.420 align:middle line:90%
It's not him.

00:32:33.420 --> 00:32:34.902 align:middle line:90%
>>Is there any doubt?

00:32:34.902 --> 00:32:36.470 align:middle line:90%
>>Let's eat.

00:32:36.470 --> 00:32:40.910 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: That scene there
was very predictive and was

00:32:40.910 --> 00:32:42.560 align:middle line:90%
very scary, actually.

00:32:42.560 --> 00:32:45.590 align:middle line:10%
>>DYER: Well, if we think about
panopticism and what it is,

00:32:45.590 --> 00:32:48.080 align:middle line:10%
this is the idea that comes
out of the 18th century

00:32:48.080 --> 00:32:50.000 align:middle line:10%
with thinkers like
Jeremy Bentham,

00:32:50.000 --> 00:32:51.500 align:middle line:10%
and he wrote that
you could actually

00:32:51.500 --> 00:32:55.040 align:middle line:10%
construct a prison with a giant
guard tower in the middle,

00:32:55.040 --> 00:32:58.730 align:middle line:10%
and you keep all of the prisoner
cells on the inside open.

00:32:58.730 --> 00:33:02.000 align:middle line:84%
And you don't let the prisoners
see when or if there are even

00:33:02.000 --> 00:33:03.290 align:middle line:90%
guards in the tower.

00:33:03.290 --> 00:33:05.600 align:middle line:84%
So if people are
under the impression

00:33:05.600 --> 00:33:07.400 align:middle line:84%
that they're always
being surveilled,

00:33:07.400 --> 00:33:10.170 align:middle line:84%
they self-police, and
they alter their behavior.

00:33:10.170 --> 00:33:12.980 align:middle line:84%
And so that was discovered
a long time ago,

00:33:12.980 --> 00:33:14.480 align:middle line:90%
and it was called panopticism.

00:33:14.480 --> 00:33:16.310 align:middle line:84%
And so this is now
the term that's

00:33:16.310 --> 00:33:19.160 align:middle line:84%
used by philosophers like
Michel Foucault for how

00:33:19.160 --> 00:33:22.780 align:middle line:84%
our system is based on NSA
mass surveillance and so forth.

00:33:22.780 --> 00:33:24.530 align:middle line:84%
And what it does is
that even though there

00:33:24.530 --> 00:33:26.634 align:middle line:84%
may not be a government
agent next to you

00:33:26.634 --> 00:33:28.550 align:middle line:84%
watching you through a
window or on a computer

00:33:28.550 --> 00:33:29.210 align:middle line:90%
or something like that--

00:33:29.210 --> 00:33:29.550 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: It doesn't matter.

00:33:29.550 --> 00:33:32.570 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: --the idea of everybody
being under surveillance causes

00:33:32.570 --> 00:33:34.355 align:middle line:84%
everybody to
self-police themselves.

00:33:34.355 --> 00:33:36.230 align:middle line:84%
And I just find it
fascinating that this film

00:33:36.230 --> 00:33:40.130 align:middle line:84%
is dominated by the dystopian
notion of panopticism and total

00:33:40.130 --> 00:33:41.060 align:middle line:90%
surveillance.

00:33:41.060 --> 00:33:43.560 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah, again, this
goes back to Plato's "Republic"

00:33:43.560 --> 00:33:46.370 align:middle line:84%
and how you would control the
population through these kinds

00:33:46.370 --> 00:33:47.720 align:middle line:90%
of mechanisms.

00:33:47.720 --> 00:33:49.850 align:middle line:84%
And I think Philip K Dick
really saw through that.

00:33:49.850 --> 00:33:50.650 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Yes.

00:33:50.650 --> 00:33:53.120 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: How we were
imprisoned by ideas

00:33:53.120 --> 00:33:54.900 align:middle line:90%
more than anything else.

00:33:54.900 --> 00:33:57.230 align:middle line:84%
So one of the big things
that people have criticized

00:33:57.230 --> 00:34:00.860 align:middle line:84%
this movie for is the
absolutely absurd ending,

00:34:00.860 --> 00:34:02.540 align:middle line:84%
where everything
just suddenly begins

00:34:02.540 --> 00:34:04.670 align:middle line:90%
going right for Tom Cruise.

00:34:04.670 --> 00:34:06.770 align:middle line:84%
And I think that that
needs to be addressed,

00:34:06.770 --> 00:34:08.780 align:middle line:84%
because I think it's
part of a sleight of hand

00:34:08.780 --> 00:34:11.929 align:middle line:84%
by Spielberg, kind of an
interesting sleight of hand.

00:34:11.929 --> 00:34:15.110 align:middle line:84%
And that is that, what
I'm contending here,

00:34:15.110 --> 00:34:20.900 align:middle line:84%
is that everything that happens
after Tom Cruise is arrested

00:34:20.900 --> 00:34:25.969 align:middle line:84%
and put into that state is
his fantasy inside that state.

00:34:25.969 --> 00:34:27.380 align:middle line:90%
Everything begins going right.

00:34:27.380 --> 00:34:28.489 align:middle line:90%
The bad guy gets caught.

00:34:28.489 --> 00:34:30.710 align:middle line:84%
He's embarrassed in
front of his friends.

00:34:30.710 --> 00:34:34.400 align:middle line:84%
His wife frees him, and
the whole scene is actually

00:34:34.400 --> 00:34:36.989 align:middle line:90%
so absurd, and it's not real.

00:34:36.989 --> 00:34:39.860 align:middle line:84%
What I'm contending is that
the last half hour the movie

00:34:39.860 --> 00:34:43.929 align:middle line:84%
is Tom Cruise's fantasy,
while he's been imprisoned.

00:34:43.929 --> 00:34:47.480 align:middle line:84%
And the guard tells him that
you're not asleep in there.

00:34:47.480 --> 00:34:48.721 align:middle line:90%
He says, you're still active.

00:34:48.721 --> 00:34:50.179 align:middle line:84%
Things are still
going on in there.

00:34:50.179 --> 00:34:52.250 align:middle line:84%
Don't for a second think
that you're just going

00:34:52.250 --> 00:34:54.139 align:middle line:90%
to fall into a dreamlike state.

00:34:54.139 --> 00:34:56.580 align:middle line:84%
And so I think that that
is what's going on here.

00:34:56.580 --> 00:34:59.450 align:middle line:84%
And again, it's very Philip K
Dickian in that the character

00:34:59.450 --> 00:35:01.370 align:middle line:84%
suddenly takes a
right turn, goes off

00:35:01.370 --> 00:35:03.260 align:middle line:84%
into a completely
other universe.

00:35:03.260 --> 00:35:05.840 align:middle line:84%
This universe, of course,
is where everything

00:35:05.840 --> 00:35:09.280 align:middle line:84%
starts going right, after a full
hour and a half of everything

00:35:09.280 --> 00:35:10.080 align:middle line:90%
going wrong.

00:35:10.080 --> 00:35:13.580 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: And Samantha Morton
ends up at this nice little cozy

00:35:13.580 --> 00:35:15.920 align:middle line:84%
cottage, and she just has
books that she can read.

00:35:15.920 --> 00:35:16.720 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Everything
is perfect.

00:35:16.720 --> 00:35:17.928 align:middle line:90%
>>DYER: Everything's perfect.

00:35:17.928 --> 00:35:20.270 align:middle line:84%
I think you're absolutely
right, and oddly enough,

00:35:20.270 --> 00:35:23.150 align:middle line:84%
there's another film
where Tom Cruise undergoes

00:35:23.150 --> 00:35:25.220 align:middle line:84%
that exact same thing
called "Vanilla Sky--"

00:35:25.220 --> 00:35:25.790 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Great film.

00:35:25.790 --> 00:35:27.915 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: --where we discover
that he's actually been

00:35:27.915 --> 00:35:31.102 align:middle line:90%
in cryogenesis for his entire--

00:35:31.102 --> 00:35:32.060 align:middle line:90%
we don't know how long.

00:35:32.060 --> 00:35:33.700 align:middle line:90%
It's centuries into the future.

00:35:33.700 --> 00:35:36.240 align:middle line:84%
There is a juxtaposition
between everything going bad,

00:35:36.240 --> 00:35:39.050 align:middle line:84%
and when he's put into
that stasis or cryogenesis

00:35:39.050 --> 00:35:42.450 align:middle line:84%
or whatever it is, it's all
some sort of mental phantasm.

00:35:42.450 --> 00:35:43.250 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: Right.

00:35:43.250 --> 00:35:44.330 align:middle line:84%
And I think people
would understand

00:35:44.330 --> 00:35:46.650 align:middle line:84%
the movie a lot better
once you understand that.

00:35:46.650 --> 00:35:50.540 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: So in my view, "Minority
Report" is Philip K Dick,

00:35:50.540 --> 00:35:53.480 align:middle line:84%
again, talking to people
from Silicon Valley back

00:35:53.480 --> 00:35:55.850 align:middle line:90%
in the day-- '60s, '70s--

00:35:55.850 --> 00:35:58.730 align:middle line:84%
and knowing where they
were going to take things.

00:35:58.730 --> 00:36:00.500 align:middle line:84%
Maybe even 50 years
ahead of time,

00:36:00.500 --> 00:36:04.280 align:middle line:84%
because what we see in this
film, even though it's what--

00:36:04.280 --> 00:36:07.010 align:middle line:90%
15, 17 years ago?

00:36:07.010 --> 00:36:08.900 align:middle line:84%
Philip K Dick was
telling us stuff

00:36:08.900 --> 00:36:11.090 align:middle line:90%
that is still yet to come.

00:36:11.090 --> 00:36:14.120 align:middle line:84%
I mean the smart cities have not
even been put into place yet,

00:36:14.120 --> 00:36:17.060 align:middle line:84%
so I see this as
yet another warning

00:36:17.060 --> 00:36:18.910 align:middle line:90%
of the dangers of technology.

00:36:18.910 --> 00:36:21.290 align:middle line:84%
I mean it can be a great
thing, but they can also

00:36:21.290 --> 00:36:24.590 align:middle line:84%
really imprison us, not so much
through some actual government

00:36:24.590 --> 00:36:27.680 align:middle line:84%
agent, but as we said,
the power of the ideas

00:36:27.680 --> 00:36:30.215 align:middle line:84%
behind mass surveillance
and panopticism.

00:36:30.215 --> 00:36:32.590 align:middle line:84%
>>WEIDNER: Yeah, I do believe
that this is both a warning

00:36:32.590 --> 00:36:35.334 align:middle line:84%
from Spielberg and Dick
about where we're headed,

00:36:35.334 --> 00:36:37.250 align:middle line:84%
and we better think about
what's going on here

00:36:37.250 --> 00:36:39.840 align:middle line:84%
real fast, because this world
is coming at us like a freight

00:36:39.840 --> 00:36:40.640 align:middle line:90%
train.

00:36:40.640 --> 00:36:43.557 align:middle line:84%
And again, there's
nobody watching the gate.

00:36:43.557 --> 00:36:45.890 align:middle line:84%
>>DYER: Join us again next
time for "Hollywood Decoded."

00:36:45.890 --> 00:36:46.820 align:middle line:90%
I'm Jay Dyer.

00:36:46.820 --> 00:36:48.111 align:middle line:90%
>>WEIDNER: And I'm Jay Weidner.

